    "description": "An embedded surface carries a Stable (or LTS) public claim only when its proof packet is within its freshness SLO, any waiver it relies on is unexpired, its evidence is complete, its claim manifest alignment is current, an owner has signed off, its boundary state is live_verified, owner/origin chrome is present, native-approval boundaries remain host-owned, and system-browser auth default is proven for identity rows. A surface that loses any of those carries a label below the cutline and never inherits an adjacent surface's published label."
